               It must have been a triumph for the great departed mycologist, the awareness that over every square mile of the inhabited earth fungi will speak of the founder of mycology for ever (or as long as this creation lasts);

For discussion of nineteenth-century concepts of multiple creations, see J. Browne (1983), especially pp. 139-44, and, for Darwin's reaction to it, pp. 199-201.
                and followed by his awareness of seeing the famous name bequeathed to a worthy son.
